109.2	Coeliac_disease	Coeliac disease	Coeliac disease (spelled celiac disease in North America and often celiac sprue) is an autoimmune disorder of the small intestine that occurs in genetically predisposed people of all ages from middle infancy onward. Symptoms include chronic diarrhoea, failure to thrive (in children), and fatigue, but these may be absent, and symptoms in other organ systems have been described.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/c/ce/Coeliac_path.jpg/230px-Coeliac_path.jpg
